      • SIGNED_RSL_URL_EXTENSION

        public static final String SIGNED_RSL_URL_EXTENSION
        The extension given to a signed RLS that is assumed to be signed. Unsigned RSLs should use the standard "swf" extension.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Configuration.RslPathInfo

        public Configuration.RslPathInfo()
        Create a new cross-domain RSL entry. The info specified the swc file to exclude put a list of RSL urls and policy file urls. The first RSL url/policy file url pair are the primary urls. The remaining urls are failovers and are only used if the primary RSL fails to load.

        Test is the url is signed.
        Parameters:
        url - url to test, the file specified by the url does not need to exist.
        Returns:
        true if the url specifies a signed rsl, false otherwise.

      • getSignedFlags

        public List<Boolean> getSignedFlags()
        Return a list of booleans that indicate if an RSL URL is signed or unsigned. There is a matching entry is this list for every entry in the RSL URL list.
        Returns:
        List of boolean signed flags for the RSL URL list. Each entry in the list is of type Boolean.
